-- Former Brazil President Jose Sarney to Undergo Heart Procedure
-- B y   G a b r i e l l e   C o p p o l a
-- 2013-08-17T17:05:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-17/former-brazil-president-jose-sarney-to-undergo-heart-procedure.html
Brazilian senator and former
president Jose Sarney will undergo a coronary catheterization on
Aug. 20 at Sirio-Libanes hospital in Sao Paulo, where he’s
currently being treated, according to a statement on the
hospital’s website.  Sarney, 83, underwent a heart exam yesterday morning that
showed a “change in the contractility in the inferior wall,”
according to the  statement .  Sarney was hospitalized July 31 for a pulmonary infection.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gabrielle Coppola in Sao Paulo at 
 gcoppola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  